      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) are directly relevant to the COU decision (structural adequacy of pedicle screw construct). Required gradation 3: QoI relevance justified by clinical and regulatory context.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness governs load sharing with the spine; yield force determines onset of permanent deformation; force at 40 mm is the ASTM F1717 regulatory endpoint. All three QoIs map directly to the FDA 510(k) substantial equivalence assessment for the device."
